strings.Value: "All right. Let's kill the troll together!"
"I can't make any promises. We need to defeat Nyrissa. But after that, if we have the time and strength..."
{n}Ekun stands near the entrance to the troll's lair, tense as a drawn bowstring.{/n} "{name}. Your journey was long, but I waited, and my wait is over."
"Wait. The witch belched poison, but truth as well. We are in the dwelling of a monster. We ought to destroy it."
"The witch came to me, poured honeyed poison into my ears. Her words besot the mind. I nearly gave in to them. But I remembered you, and decided to wait."
"It will be as you decide. The witch is scarier than the troll. She sows death as grain. Defeating her is more important. You lead, I follow."
"When it's time to hunt, animals form packs. A pack is led by a leader. You have led me through the path of {d|Ekun Hunt}revenge{/d}, you will lead me from here."

"Rage has already led me on the wrong path, but you {d|Ekun Ritual}didn't let{/d} it take control. Your voice in my mind was stronger than the witch's voice. I fight for what is precious and needs protection, not for the sake of fighting. Not to relieve the pain."
